  "doc_id": "59807",
  "text": "The complement system is an important mediator involved in experimental I/R injury in animals. In a rat model of reperfusion injury of ischaemic myocardium, prevention of complement activation resulted in a pronounced reduction of I/R related injury. [CITATION_1] In addition, there is preliminary evidence that the inhibition of complement by C1 inhibitor reduces infarction size by up to 57% in humans. [CITATION_2] These results point to complement as an attractive target for limiting I/R injury. However, the molecular basis of I/R induced complement activation is not completely understood.",
